thread.title: Former New York Fed Chief William McDonough, Who Guided Bank Through 9/11, Dies

author: Michael S. Derby
title: Former New York Fed Chief William McDonough, Who Guided Bank Through 9/11, Dies
text:
William McDonough, who led the Federal Reserve Bank of New York through the Sept. 11, 2001, terrorist attacks and their aftermath, died Tuesday.
Mr. McDonough, 83 years old, died at his home in Waccabuc, N.Y., the New York Fed said Thursday. The bank didnâ€™t give a cause of death.
